Hello,

We have a few remaining seats available on the following hybrid course 
(you can attended in person or simultaneously via Zoom):

Multivariate Analysis -Integrating Classical Techniques with 
multivariate GLMM.

When: 13 - 16 May 2024.
Where: Wageningen, The Netherlands.
Course flyer: 
https://www.highstat.com/Courses/Flyers/Flyer2024_05_MultivariateAnalysis.pdf

Registration: www.highstat.com

*
*

*Outline:*

We start with classical multivariate techniques like principal component 
analysis and redundancy analysis. We then continue with generalised 
linear latent variable models (GLLVM). A GLLVM is a GLM (or GLMM) in 
which multiple response variables are analysed simultaneously, while 
allowing for dependency between the response variables and also between 
the observations. We will discuss extensions of GLLVM that allow for 
constrained latent variables (concurrent ordination) and spatial and 
temporal dependency structures

